{"type":"message","id":"cf49e92b","parentId":"bd1d2cc2","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:16.069Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the qqbot-media skill isn't at that path. Let me find it. Also the images from Son's draw directory are not in the media/qqbot directory. The MEDIA directive likely looks for files in the media directory, not in arbitrary paths.\n\nSo the issue is clear:\n1. Son saved images in `~/.openclaw/workspace-son/draw/` \n2. When I used `MEDIA:/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/draw/draw_00001.png` - this absolute path likely doesn't work because the MEDIA directive expects files in a specific media directory\n3. Son returned `MEDIA:draw/draw_DRAW-20260605-00002.png` - relative path from workspace-son, but since Son's results are auto-announced, the MEDIA directive needs the file to be accessible from the correct media directory\n\nLet me find the actual skill file for qqbot media.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Q3Q2bt2x1Q90uyexgqBd4645","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw -name \"qqbot*\" -type f 2>/dev/null | head -20"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"find /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw -name \\\"qqbot*\\\" -type f 2>/dev/null | head -20\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01_sqabnrpacos9MfjSG2Om6799","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/ 2>/dev/null"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"ls /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/ 2>/dev/null\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":2017,"output":320,"cacheRead":63488,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":202,"totalTokens":65825,"cost":{"input":0.00028238000000000004,"output":0.00008960000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001777664,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002149644}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780603391957,"responseId":"8c201c65-46c6-4a8b-aeb2-2925c69ee510"}}
