{"type":"message","id":"06241d9e","parentId":"fc6c37c9","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:23.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No qqbot-media skill in the skills directory. The MEDIA directive is likely handled by the qqbot channel itself, not a skill.\n\nLet me look at the qqbot channel docs for info about MEDIA directive.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_5OmxeEwKk2m5yPbqivrf8522","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/qqbot.md","limit":80},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/qqbot.md\", \"limit\": 80}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":315,"output":121,"cacheRead":65792,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":47,"totalTokens":66228,"cost":{"input":0.0000441,"output":0.00003388,"cacheRead":0.001842176,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0019201560000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780603401209,"responseId":"b8ce3993-f397-42e7-a153-ff3fc8d0ec03"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4382562","parentId":"06241d9e","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:24.352Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_5OmxeEwKk2m5yPbqivrf8522","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"QQ Bot setup, config, and usage\"\nread_when:\n  - You want to connect OpenClaw to QQ\n  - You need QQ Bot credential setup\n  - You want QQ Bot group or private chat support\ntitle: QQ bot\n---\n\nQQ Bot connects to OpenClaw via the official QQ Bot API (WebSocket gateway). The\nplugin supports C2C private chat, group @messages, and guild channel messages with\nrich media (images, voice, video, files).\n\nStatus: downloadable plugin. Direct messages, group chats, guild channels, and\nmedia are supported. Reactions and threads are not supported.\n\n## Install\n\nInstall QQ Bot before setup:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw plugins install @openclaw/qqbot\n```\n\n## Setup\n\n1. Go to the [QQ Open Platform](https://q.qq.com/) and scan the QR code with your\n   phone QQ to register / log in.\n2. Click **Create Bot** to create a new QQ bot.\n3. Find **AppID** and **AppSecret** on the bot's settings page and copy them.\n\n> AppSecret is not stored in plaintext — if you leave the page without saving it,\n> you'll have to regenerate a new one.\n\n4. Add the channel:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels add --channel qqbot --token \"***\"\n```\n\n5. Restart the Gateway.\n\nInteractive setup paths:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels add\nopenclaw configure --section channels\n```\n\n## Configure\n\nMinimal config:\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    qqbot: {\n      enabled: true,\n      appId: \"YOUR_APP_ID\",\n      clientSecret: \"***\",\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nDefault-account env vars:\n\n- `QQBOT_APP_ID`\n- `QQBOT_CLIENT_SECRET`\n\nFile-backed AppSecret:\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    qqbot: {\n      enabled: true,\n      appId: \"YOUR_APP_ID\",\n      clientSecretFile: \"/path/to/qqbot-secret.txt\",\n    },\n\n[230 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780603404350}}
{"type":"message","id":"692abb96","parentId":"a4382562","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:26.504Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me search for MEDIA in the qqbot docs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_5PT9AwIq1vOGtVNd09hv3604","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n -i \"media\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/qqbot.md | head -20"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -n -i \\\"media\\\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/qqbot.md | head -20\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01_Yyvmm08nohoGS9l6bMF43132","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"MEDIA\\|media\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/qqbot.md | head -20"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -rn \\\"MEDIA\\\\|media\\\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/qqbot.md | head -20\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":530,"output":142,"cacheRead":66176,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":13,"totalTokens":66848,"cost":{"input":0.0000742,"output":0.000039760000000000006,"cacheRead":0.001852928,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001966888}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780603404387,"responseId":"30468501-12e0-4ace-9bb1-7bd8beebd794"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f9cc81d","parentId":"692abb96","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:30.365Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_5PT9AwIq1vOGtVNd09hv3604","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"12:rich media (images, voice, video, files).\n15:media are supported. Reactions and threads are not supported.\n195:| STT     | `channels.qqbot.stt`                                     | `tools.media.audio.models[0]` |\n229:Inbound QQ voice attachments are exposed to agents as audio media metadata while\n230:keeping raw voice files out of generic `MediaPaths`. `[[audio_as_voice]]` plain\n274:- Each account owns an isolated resource stack (WebSocket connection, API client, token cache, media storage root) keyed by `appId`. Accounts never share inbound/outbound state.\n276:- Inbound, outbound, and gateway bridge paths share a single media payload root under `~/.openclaw/media`, so uploads, downloads, and transcode caches land under one guarded directory instead of a per-subsystem tree.\n277:- Rich media delivery goes through one `sendMedia` path for C2C and group targets. Local files and buffers above the large-file threshold use QQ's chunked upload endpoints, while smaller payloads use the one-shot media API."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1209,"aggregated":"12:rich media (images, voice, video, files).\n15:media are supported. Reactions and threads are not supported.\n195:| STT     | `channels.qqbot.stt`                                     | `tools.media.audio.models[0]` |\n229:Inbound QQ voice attachments are exposed to agents as audio media metadata while\n230:keeping raw voice files out of generic `MediaPaths`. `[[audio_as_voice]]` plain\n274:- Each account owns an isolated resource stack (WebSocket connection, API client, token cache, media storage root) keyed by `appId`. Accounts never share inbound/outbound state.\n276:- Inbound, outbound, and gateway bridge paths share a single media payload root under `~/.op