{"type":"message","id":"80e03695","parentId":"db6ab9f5","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:33.715Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the MEDIA directive is part of the framework's mechanism. It seems the MEDIA: prefix is used to attach media files in the assistant's response, and the framework handles uploading the file to the channel.\n\nThe media directory is `~/.openclaw/media/` and it's shared across accounts.\n\nThe thing is - when I used `MEDIA:/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/draw/draw_00001.png`, the file needs to be accessible. It's in Son's workspace, not in the media directory.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to reference files from workspace-son or if I need to copy them to the media directory first.\n\nActually, the MEDIA directive format should work with any path, not just the media directory. Let me check if there's any documentation about the MEDIA syntax.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_kzzVRz26Lrnqkqfghnof9860","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"MEDIA\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ --include=\"*.md\" | head -30"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -rn \\\"MEDIA\\\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ --include=\\\"*.md\\\" | head -30\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":499,"output":246,"cacheRead":66816,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":175,"totalTokens":67561,"cost":{"input":0.00006986,"output":0.00006888,"cacheRead":0.001870848,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002009588}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780603410409,"responseId":"fe6ad2da-57b2-4e11-9840-a575efb4c998"}}
{"type":"message","id":"867c6268","parentId":"80e03695","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:35.985Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_kzzVRz26Lrnqkqfghnof9860","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:5:  - Debugging `[embed ...]`, `MEDIA:`, reply, or audio presentation directives\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:11:- `MEDIA:` for attachment delivery\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:16:Remote `MEDIA:` attachments must be public `https:` URLs. Plain `http:`,\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:20:Local `MEDIA:` attachments can use absolute paths, workspace-relative paths, or\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:25:`MEDIA:` is parsed only as plain text. Wrapping the directive in Markdown\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:32:MEDIA:/workspace/image.png\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:38:**MEDIA:/workspace/image.png**\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:39:`MEDIA:/workspace/image.png`\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:40:Here is your image: MEDIA:/workspace/image.png\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:43:Keep `MEDIA:` on its own line, in plain text, with no surrounding formatting.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:50:These directives are separate. `MEDIA:` and reply/voice tags remain delivery metadata; `[embed ...]` is the web-only rich render path.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:51:Trusted tool-result media uses the same `MEDIA:` / `[[audio_as_voice]]` parser before delivery, so text tool outputs can still mark an audio attachment as a voice note.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:53:When block streaming is enabled, `MEDIA:` remains single-delivery metadata for a\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:75:- `MEDIA:` is not an embed alias and should not be used for rich embed rendering.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:57:`MEDIA:` directives are normal delivery metadata. When block streaming sends a\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:65:notes or files on channels such as Telegram when an agent emits `MEDIA:` during\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1740:    Outbound attachments from the agent must include a `MEDIA:<path-or-url>` line (on its own line). See [OpenClaw assistant setup](/start/openclaw) and [Agent send](/tools/agent-send).\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1753:    - `tools.fs.workspaceOnly=false` lets `MEDIA:` send host-local files the agent can already read, but only for media plus safe document types (images, audio, video, PDF, and Office docs). Plain text and secret-like files are still blocked.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/browser-control.md:249:- `--labels` adds a viewport-only screenshot with overlayed ref labels (prints `MEDIA:<path>`).\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:736:- Skips TTS if the reply already contains media or a `MEDIA:` directive.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:751:  yes -> has media / MEDIA: / short?\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/index.md:189:Higher-level helpers exist for the common \"give the agent a MEDIA attachment\" workflows.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/index.md:221:CLI helper (writes to a temp file and prints `MEDIA:<path>`):\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/index.md:260:openclaw nodes camera snap --node <idOrNameOrIp>            # default: both facings (2 MEDIA lines)\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:5:  - Extending agent-accessible MEDIA temp-file workflows\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:62:### CLI helper (temp files + MEDIA)\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:64:The easiest way to get attachments is via the CLI helper, which writes decoded media to a temp file and prints `MEDIA:<path>`.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:69:openclaw nodes camera snap --node <id>               # default: both front + back (2 MEDIA lines)\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:129:openclaw nodes camera snap --node <id>            # prints MEDIA:<path>\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:133:openclaw nodes camera clip --node <id> --duration 10s          # prints MEDIA:<path>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1108,"aggregated":"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:5:  - Debugging `[embed ...]`, `MEDIA:`, reply, or audio presentation directives\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:11:- `MEDIA:` for attachment delivery\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:16:Remote `MEDIA:` attachments must be public `https:` URLs. Plain `http:`,\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:20:Local `MEDIA:` attachments can use absolute paths, workspace-relative paths, or\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:25:`MEDIA:` is parsed only as plain text. Wrapping the directive in Markdown\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:32:MEDIA:/workspace/image.png\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md:38:**MEDIA:/workspace/image.png**\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-proto