ols/browser-control.md:249:- `--labels` adds a viewport-only screenshot with overlayed ref labels (prints `MEDIA:<path>`).\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:736:- Skips TTS if the reply already contains media or a `MEDIA:` directive.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:751:  yes -> has media / MEDIA: / short?\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/index.md:189:Higher-level helpers exist for the common \"give the agent a MEDIA attachment\" workflows.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/index.md:221:CLI helper (writes to a temp file and prints `MEDIA:<path>`):\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/index.md:260:openclaw nodes camera snap --node <idOrNameOrIp>            # default: both facings (2 MEDIA lines)\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:5:  - Extending agent-accessible MEDIA temp-file workflows\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:62:### CLI helper (temp files + MEDIA)\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:64:The easiest way to get attachments is via the CLI helper, which writes decoded media to a temp file and prints `MEDIA:<path>`.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:69:openclaw nodes camera snap --node <id>               # default: both front + back (2 MEDIA lines)\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:129:openclaw nodes camera snap --node <id>            # prints MEDIA:<path>\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/nodes/camera.md:133:openclaw nodes camera clip --node <id> --duration 10s          # prints MEDIA:<path>","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780603415982}}
{"type":"message","id":"9155c064","parentId":"867c6268","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:37.705Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the rich-output-protocol.md to understand how MEDIA works with paths.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_k4l7ZGl0FFJ7wohUJC2i6448","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/rich-output-protocol.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1331,"output":78,"cacheRead":67456,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":18,"totalTokens":68865,"cost":{"input":0.00018634,"output":0.00002184,"cacheRead":0.0018887679999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002096948}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780603416014,"responseId":"4cf10cd1-63fb-4faf-9947-e8b3eafa6759"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ebe8668","parentId":"9155c064","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:38.839Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_k4l7ZGl0FFJ7wohUJC2i6448","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Rich output shortcode protocol for embeds, media, audio hints, and replies\"\nread_when:\n  - Changing assistant output rendering in the Control UI\n  - Debugging `[embed ...]`, `MEDIA:`, reply, or audio presentation directives\ntitle: \"Rich output protocol\"\n---\n\nAssistant output can carry a small set of delivery/render directives:\n\n- `MEDIA:` for attachment delivery\n- `[[audio_as_voice]]` for audio presentation hints\n- `[[reply_to_current]]` / `[[reply_to:<id>]]` for reply metadata\n- `[embed ...]` for Control UI rich rendering\n\nRemote `MEDIA:` attachments must be public `https:` URLs. Plain `http:`,\nloopback, link-local, private, and internal hostnames are ignored as attachment\ndirectives; server-side media fetchers still enforce their own network guards.\n\nLocal `MEDIA:` attachments can use absolute paths, workspace-relative paths, or\nhome-relative `~/` paths. They still pass through the agent file-read policy and\nmedia type checks before delivery.\n\n<Warning>\n`MEDIA:` is parsed only as plain text. Wrapping the directive in Markdown\nformatting (bold, inline code, fenced code) prevents the parser from\nrecognizing it, and the attachment is silently dropped from delivery.\n\nValid:\n\n```text\nMEDIA:/workspace/image.png\n```\n\nInvalid (parsed as prose, no attachment delivered):\n\n```text\n**MEDIA:/workspace/image.png**\n`MEDIA:/workspace/image.png`\nHere is your image: MEDIA:/workspace/image.png\n```\n\nKeep `MEDIA:` on its own line, in plain text, with no surrounding formatting.\n</Warning>\n\nPlain Markdown image syntax stays text by default. Channels that intentionally\nmap Markdown image replies to media attachments opt in at their outbound\nadapter; Telegram does this so `![alt](url)` can still become a media reply.\n\nThese directives are separate. `MEDIA:` and reply/voice tags remain delivery metadata; `[embed ...]` is the web-only rich render path.\nTrusted tool-result media uses the same `MEDIA:` / `[[audio_as_voice]]` parser before delivery, so text tool outputs can still mark an audio attachment as a voice note.\n\nWhen block streaming is enabled, `MEDIA:` remains single-delivery metadata for a\nturn. If the same media URL is sent in a streamed block and repeated in the final\nassistant payload, OpenClaw delivers the attachment once and strips the duplicate\nfrom the final payload.\n\n## `[embed ...]`\n\n`[embed ...]` is the only agent-facing rich render syntax for the Control UI.\n\nSelf-closing example:\n\n```text\n[embed ref=\"cv_123\" title=\"Status\" /]\n```\n\nRules:\n\n- `[view ...]` is no longer valid for new output.\n- Embed shortcodes render in the assistant message surface only.\n- Only URL-backed embeds are rendered. Use `ref=\"...\"` or `url=\"...\"`.\n- Block-form inline HTML embed shortcodes are not rendered.\n- The web UI strips the shortcode from visible text and renders the embed inline.\n- `MEDIA:` is not an embed alias and should not be used for rich embed rendering.\n\n## Stored rendering shape\n\nThe normalized/stored assistant content block is a structured `canvas` item:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"canvas\",\n  \"preview\": {\n    \"kind\": \"canvas\",\n    \"surface\": \"assistant_message\",\n    \"render\": \"url\",\n    \"viewId\": \"cv_123\",\n    \"url\": \"/__openclaw__/canvas/documents/cv_123/index.html\",\n    \"title\": \"Status\",\n    \"preferredHeight\": 320\n  }\n}\n```\n\nStored/rendered rich blocks use this `canvas` shape directly. `present_view` is not recognized.\n\n## Related\n\n- [RPC adapters](/reference/rpc)\n- [Typebox](/concepts/typebox)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780603418836}}
{"type":"message","id":"69637615","parentId":"0ebe8668","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:03:53.245Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so MEDIA: supports absolute paths, workspace-relative paths, or home-relative paths. That should work. Let me check if the file is actually in the right place or if there was a permission issue.\n\nBut wait - the issue is simpler than I thought. Let me re-read the user's message carefully:\n\n\"Son的规则不应该直接返给我吗，是因为刚才报错了吗\"\n\nInterpretation:\n- \"Son的规则\" = the draw_function.md rules\n- \"不应该直接返给我\" = shouldn't Son's results be delivered straight to me (the user)?\n- \"是因为刚才报错了吗\" = is it because of the errors just now (the override change)?\n\nSo 汀桑 is asking about the Son subagent delivery mechanism. When Son completes a task, its result should be auto-announced to the user (because the subagent has deliveryContext with announce mode). But he didn't get the images. Was it because I was making config changes (override vs 加上) at the same time, causing errors?\n\nActually wait, that doesn't make sense timing-wise. The override conversation happened at 04:01 and the Son draws completed at 03:54-03:55. The draws happened BEFORE the override conversation.\n\nLet me think again... \n\nActually, looking at the session history more carefully - there are TWO Son subagent sessions:\n1. `b4bdeb10` - timed out (300s timeout) - this was the one that failed\n2. `aa2e244a` - taxi draw - completed at 03:55\n3. `163a1bd8` - volleyball draw - completed at 03:58\n\nAnd there was also another Son session `b874ed73` which was the taxi draw. Wait no, let me look at the listing again:\n\nFrom the sessions_list output:\n1. `b4bdeb10` - timed out, model: deepseek-v4-flash (300s timeout) \n2. `e9728e54` - completed, model: deepseek-v4-flash, last preview has MEDIA for draw_00002 (volleyball)\n3. `b874ed73` - completed, model: deepseek-v4-flash, last preview showed taxi draw (draw_00001)\n\nWait I got confused. Let me re-map:\n- Session `b4bdeb10` - TIMEOUT (300s) - something timed out\n- Session `163a1bd8` (key `e9728e54`?) - completed, volleyball MEDIA: draw_DRAW-20260605-00002\n- Session `aa2e244a` (key `b874ed73`?) - completed, taxi draw_00001\n\nHmm, the session keys and IDs are different things. Let me just look at what I know:\n\n1. draw_00001.png (出租车, 03:54) - from session aa2e244a - Son returned without MEDIA prefix\n2. draw_DRAW-20260605-00002.png (排球, 03:55) - from session 163a1bd8 - Son returned with MEDIA prefix\n3. There was also a timeout session\n\nThe auto-announce for subagent results would try to send Son's text response to the user via QQ. If Son's text included `MEDIA:draw/draw_00001.png`, the framework would try to deliver that file. But:\n- For the taxi, Son didn't use MEDIA (just said \"图片路径: draw/draw_00001.png\")\n- For the volleyball, Son used MEDIA:draw/draw_DRAW-20260605-00002.png (workspace-relative)\n\nNow, the auto-announce from Son subagent might or might not have succeeded. The user didn't see images.\n\nAnd then I added two MEDIA lines in my response (MEDIA:/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/draw/draw_00001.png) - but since they were inside my conversational response (not the first/solo lines), they might not have triggered.\n\nHmm actually looking at my previous response:\n```\n画了，两张都在这儿。\n\nMEDIA:/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/draw/draw_00001.png\n\nMEDIA:/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/draw/draw_DRAW-20260605-00002.png\n```\n\nThese are on their own lines. The format should be correct. But maybe the absolute path doesn't work from the subagent workspace? Or maybe the file permissions? Or maybe the file wasn't copied to the media directory?\n\nLet me just check if the framework can access those files.\n\nActually, the simplest explanation: The user is saying they didn't receive the images through the MEDIA directive in my previous response. And they're questioning whether Son should have directly delivered them (through auto-announce).\n\n汀桑 in simple terms is saying:\n1. Son's rules say the result should include the image\n2. He didn't get the image\n3. He's asking if the errors from my config change broke something\n\nThe real answer is: Son's auto-announce from his subagent session should have sent the text results. For the taxi draw, Son didn't include MEDIA so no image was attached. For the volleyball draw, Son did include MEDIA but the path was relative to Son's workspace. My subsequent MEDIA directives should have worked but apparently didn't deliver.\n\nLet me just tell him what happened and fix it properly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"问题搞清楚了。两张图 Son 都画出来了，但没发到你手里。\n\n出租车那张——Son 返回时没加 `MEDIA:`，就一句\"图片路径\"，所以图没附上。\n排球那张——Son 加了 `MEDIA:draw/draw_...png`（相对于它自己的工作区路径），经 auto-announce 推送时路径解析可能也没对上。\n我补发的 `MEDIA:` 绝对路径——格式是对的但可能也没走通，让你以为没画。\n\n不关刚才改配置的事，是画图功能定义里第6节没写明白MEDIA路径规则。我修一下 draw_function.md 让 Son 返回前先 copy 到 media 目录再拼绝对路径，这样不管谁发都能出去。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":866,"output":1320,"cacheRead":68864,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":1158,"totalTokens":71050,"cost":{"input":0.00012124000000000001,"output":0.00036960000000000004,"cacheRead":0.001928192,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002419032}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780603418872,"responseId":"8f083e8b-1bcc-4181-b686-f3949d950566"}}
