{"type":"message","id":"04db9fc4","parentId":"1cfe3b2a","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:07:07.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so let me understand the current flow:\n\n1. Son's subagent sessions have auto-announce built into their delivery context. When I `sessions_spawn(agentId: \"son\", ...)`, the spawned subagent gets deliveryContext copied from the parent session, which includes `{channel: \"qqbot\", to: \"qqbot:c2c:6687...\", accountId: \"bot1\"}`. This means Son's results get announced directly to the user.\n\n2. The functions that use MEDIA are:\n   - `album_function.md` - line 67 (save): `MEDIA:album/images/{sender_id}/{ID}.{ext}`\n   - `album_function.md` - line 88 (view): `MEDIA:album/images/{sender_id}/{filename}`\n   - `album_function.md` - line 137: doc comment about MEDIA\n   - `draw_function.md` - need to check\n\nLet me also check draw_function.md and compose_function.md for MEDIA usage.\n\n汀桑 wants:\n1. Remove Son's auto-announce logic - all Son results go to Father first\n2. Father forwards to user\n3. All function definition files need to be updated for this new workflow\n\nThe changes needed:\n\n**A. Son function definition files**: \nRemove MEDIA prefix from return format. Instead, return structured info about the file path + text.\n\n**B. Father AGENTS.md**:\nAfter receiving Son's result, parse the file path and emit MEDIA directive.\n\n**C. Son spawn configuration**:\nNeed to ensure subagent sessions don't auto-announce. When spawning, should I use `delivery: {mode: \"none\"}` or is there another mechanism?\n\nLet me check how sessions_spawn works and if there's a way to suppress announce.\n\nActually, looking at the sessions_spawn tool description, there's no explicit option to suppress auto-announce. The auto-announce might be inherent to the subagent's delivery context being inherited from the parent.\n\nHmm, but maybe I can set delivery mode in the cron config, or maybe I need to change something in how Son is configured.\n\nActually, I think the key issue might be simpler. Let me check the Son agent config for any auto-announce settings.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_uZEQ4Z68n2QYHWKsfJ1Q6845","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"MEDIA\\|media\\|deliver\\|announce\\|auto\" ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/functions/draw_function.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -n \\\"MEDIA\\\\|media\\\\|deliver\\\\|announce\\\\|auto\\\" ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/functions/draw_function.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01_HGpHyyeBL05kJQN8dkqf5546","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"MEDIA\\|media\\|deliver\\|announce\\|auto\\|qqmedia\" ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/functions/compose_function.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -n \\\"MEDIA\\\\|media\\\\|deliver\\\\|announce\\\\|auto\\\\|qqmedia\\\" ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/functions/compose_function.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_02_bgS0kVuT03zuOKkr78nl0544","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/functions_manifest.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/functions_manifest.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_03_CtxfVmzNaI2H2uR9P5up9563","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/son/config.yaml 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/agents/son/config.json 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/agent.yaml 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/config.yaml 2>/dev/null || echo \"NO_CONFIG_FOUND\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/son/config.yaml 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/agents/son/config.json 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/agent.yaml 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/config.yaml 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"NO_CONFIG_FOUND\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":435,"output":772,"cacheRead":72064,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":477,"totalTokens":73271,"cost