{"type":"message","id":"85a41989","parentId":"81c24d7b","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:07:22.960Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK let me understand the full picture:\n\n1. Son's functions with MEDIA:\n   - `album_function.md` - save/view actions return MEDIA prefix\n   - `draw_function.md` - need to check for MEDIA (grep returned empty though)\n   - `compose_function.md` - copies mp3 to `~/.openclaw/media/qqbot/` for `<qqmedia>` tags\n\n2. When I `sessions_spawn(agentId: \"son\", ...)`, the subagent inherits the parent session's delivery context. This auto-announces Son's results to the user.\n\n汀桑 wants to change this so:\n- Son's results always come back to Father first\n- Father does the MEDIA/file forwarding\n\nSo the plan is:\n\n**Step 1: Fix Son's spawn mechanism** - When I spawn Son, I need the result to come back to me (Father) instead of auto-announcing to user. But sessions_spawn doesn't have an explicit \"don't announce\" option...\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the sessions_spawn tool description:\n- `delivery` in cron: has `mode: \"announce\" | \"webhook\" | \"none\"`\n- But sessions_spawn doesn't have a delivery parameter\n\nHmm, but the behavior described in the tool says: \"Results auto-announce to your requester\". So the subagent's delivery context is inherited.\n\nActually, maybe the way to handle this is simpler than I thought. The Son subagent returns its result text to Father as a completion event. Father gets the result and can then forward it. The auto-announce might send the text result to the user simultaneously.\n\nLet me think about what exactly needs to change:\n\n1. **Son function definition files** - Remove MEDIA prefix from return format. Instead just return text + file path info. This way if auto-announce fires, the user only gets text, not a broken attachment.\n\n2. **Father's logic** - After `sessions_yield` gets Son's result, Father reads the result, extracts file paths, copies files to media/qqbot/ if needed, and emits MEDIA prefixes in its own response.\n\n3. **Compose** - Already copies files to `~/.openclaw/media/qqbot/` which is good. The `<qqmedia>` tags should work from there.\n\nBut actually, I'm overcomplicating this. Let me re-read what the user said:\n\n\"去除Son自己Announce的逻辑，统一先转给你，几个功能定义文件改完整\"\n\n\"先转给你\" = Son的结果先转给我（Father）\n\"几个功能定义文件改完整\" = 所有功能定义文件统一改\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Change the architecture so Son returns to Father, not directly to user\n2. Update all function definitions to not include MEDIA in their return format\n3. Father handles the final delivery\n\nBut how do I \"remove Son's announce logic\"? Is there a config option for this?\n\nLet me check if there's an agent config for Son that controls auto-announce behavior.\n\nActually, I should look at the Gateway agent configuration.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_L6P8hUAftaYubQEqrFG39439","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"auto.announce\\|autoAnnounce\\|delivery\\|announce\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/agents/ --include=\"*.md\" 2>/dev/null | head -20"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -rn \\\"auto.announce\\\\|autoAnnounce\\\\|delivery\\\\|announce\\\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/agents/ --include=\\\"*.md\\\" 2>/dev/null | head -20\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01_qIp8woHPy3Qezj3jPZyu9405","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.yaml\" -o -name \"*.json\" | grep -i son | head -10"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"find ~/.openclaw -name \\\"*.yaml\\\" -o -name \\\"*.json\\\" | grep -i son | head -10\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":739,"output":811,"cacheRead":73216,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":664,"totalTokens":74766,"cost":{"input":0.00010346,"output":0.00022708000000000003,"cacheRead":0.002050048,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0023805880000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780603634