{"type":"message","id":"503e77cf","parentId":"640b3ea3","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:22:49.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but I used album save for pure image analysis. That's not right either. The album save action would save the image to the album which the user didn't ask for. I need a dedicated action for \"just analyze this image without saving.\"\n\nBut we don't have that function defined. I should create one. Or I could just add a new action to the album function - like \"analyze\" that just does the VL image analysis without saving.\n\nActually, the original issue 汀桑 was asking about is simpler - he just wants me to specify the model override in the rule. The existing spawn approach (album save) is fine for now because it does analyze the image via VL - it just also saves it. But for pure image analysis, saving is fine since it stores the image in the album.\n\nActually no, for pure image messages, the user might not want the image saved. They just want it described. So I should either:\n1. Add an \"analyze\" action to album function that only analyzes without saving\n2. Or just use a different approach\n\nHmm, but for now the rule I just wrote is using album save. That's what I spawned earlier too. The image got analyzed and saved. It's a reasonable default - if user sends a picture, save it to album + describe it.\n\nActually, the Son subagent result I just got back said \"no image data provided\" because when I spawned Son, I didn't include the image attachment. The attachment needs to be passed in the spawn.\n\nFor spawn with image attachment, I need to figure out how to pass the file path... Looking at sessions_spawn, there's no explicit attachment parameter. But Son might be able to read the file from the media path since it's accessible from the filesystem. Let me check the album save function - in step 1, it says \"从上下文消息中获取图片附件\". \n\nBut there's no image in the spawn context - I need to either pass the path in params or find another way.\n\nActually, for pure images, I should just use the `image` tool myself since I can access the media files directly. That's what I did and it worked fine. Spawning Son with VL for pure image analysis is overengineering it.\n\nBut 汀桑 wanted the rule to say to spawn Son. Let me just follow what he wants and make the rule correct.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"等等，不对。纯图片分析用 album save 不合适——用户没叫存。我重写这条规则，加个轻量的分析行为。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_1XlhIPlNvPXpNR5752uG2603","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md","edits":[{"oldText":"      ├─ 纯图片消息（用户只发了图、无文字指令）→ spawn Son 用 VL 模型分析原图\n          sessions_spawn(\n            agentId: \"son\",\n            model: \"dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash\",\n            task: '{\"function\":\"album\",\"action\":\"save\",\"params\":{\"annotation\":\"\",\"sender_id\":\"{sender_id}\"}}',\n            mode: \"run\"\n          )\n          → 等 Son 结果返回图片描述 + FILE 路径 → 按 3.3 Step 3 规则转发","newText":"      ├─ 纯图片消息（用户只发了图、无文字指令）→ 直接 spawn Son 用 VL 模型分析原图，返回图片内容描述\n          sessions_spawn(\n            agentId: \"son\",\n            model: \"dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash\",\n            task: '{\"function\":\"album\",\"action\":\"save\",\"params\":{\"annotation\":\"\",\"sender_id\":\"汀桑的ID\"}}',\n            mode: \"run\"\n          )\n          → 等 Son 返回 FILE: 路径 + 文本 → 按 3.3 Step 3 转发"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\":\"      ├─ 纯图片消息（用户只发了图、无文字指令）→ spawn Son 用 VL 模型分析原图\\n          sessions_spawn(\\n            agentId: \\\"son\\\",\\n            model: \\\"dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash\\\",\\n            task: '{\\\"function\\\":\\\"album\\\",\\\"action\\\":\\\"save\\\",\\\"params\\\":{\\\"annotation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"sender_id\\\":\\\"{sender_id}\\\"}}',\\n            mode: \\\"run\\\"\\n          )\\n          → 等 Son 结果返回图片描述 + FILE 路径 → 按 3.3 Step 3 规则转发\",\"newText