{"type":"message","id":"827c2e92","parentId":"a6cbe2a9","timestamp":"2026-06-04T20:23:00.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK but I still have the issue that album save saves the image too. Let me think about this differently.\n\nActually, saving is fine - it's a passive album function. When user sends a random image, saving it to the album with an empty annotation and just using the VL analysis as description is reasonable. The user can always delete it later. And the primary function is still \"describe the image\" via VL.\n\nAlso, the spinner for Son might not find the image in its context since it was sent to me (Father's session), not to Son. I need to figure out how to pass the image path to Son.\n\nHmm, I already saw this issue - the Son result said \"no image data\". So I need to either:\n1. Have Son read the image from a known path\n2. Or use a different mechanism\n\nActually, look at how the album save action works - step 1 says \"从上下文消息中获取图片附件\". If Son doesn't have the image in its context, it can't save it.\n\nFor pure image analysis, the simplest approach that works is: **I use the image tool directly** since I have access to the media files. Spawning Son with VL is architecturally correct but practically requires passing the image path which the current spawn mechanism doesn't support well.\n\nLet me just tell 汀桑 this - the rule says spawn Son but Son can't see the image because it's in my session, not Son's. The image tool on my end works directly.\n\nActually wait, I should be practical. Let me just tell 汀桑 the situation and ask him how he wants to handle it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"汀桑，还有个实际问题。sl\n\n纯图片 spawn Son 的话，图在**我的 session 里**，Son 拿不到附件路径。刚才我 spawn 的那次 album save 就报\"没有图片数据\"了。\n\n可行的方案：\n\n**A.** 我先 spawn Son（VL override），在 task params 里把图片的绝对路径传过去，Son 自己去读文件做 VL 分析  \n**B.** 纯图片我自己直接调 image tool 看了回你，不走 Son  \n**C.** 给 Son 加一个专门的 analyze_image 功能定义，params 